---

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the pasta.

Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into four long strips then chop widthways into roughly 2cm pieces.

Trim the @courgette{1} then halve lengthways. Thinly slice widthways into 2cm thick half moons.

Pop both onto a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, spread out and roast on the top shelf until soft, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Add the @linguine{200%g} to the pan of boiling water and cook until tender, ~{12%minutes} then drain in a #colander{}.

Pop back in the pan, drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one).

Finely chop the @chives{1}(finely chopped) (or use #scissors{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat. When hot, add the @chorizo{60%g}, fry until the chorizo is golden, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic and cook, stirring, for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @tomato puree{30%g}, followed by the @finely chopped tomatoes with basil{1}, @vegetable stock powder{1}, @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g} and @water{50%ml}.

Add a pinch of @sugar{pinch} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thick and tomatoey, ~{4-5%minutes}.

When they are ready, combine the roasted veggies, cooked pasta and sauce in whichever saucepan is the largest.

Stir in half the chives and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}.

> TIP: Add a splash more water if it seems a bit dry!

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Serve in #bowls{}. Finish with the @walnuts{20%g} and a sprinkling of the remaining chives and cheese. Enjoy!

== Step 4 MOD ==

If you've added chorizo to your meal, add to the pan before you add the garlic, tomato puree etc.

Fry until the chorizo is golden, ~{2-3%minutes}, add the garlic, cook for ~{30%seconds} stirring frequently. Continue with the rest of the step and recipe as instructed.